## 2. Event-Driven ECC Registration

Executing ECC Registration via `cv2.findTransformECC` is computationally intensive.

**Solution:**
The [PrecisionAligner](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260309/fire_detection/video_confusion_rtsp.py#107-141) is instantiated as a non-blocking background thread. Under stable conditions, it re-computes the spatial Affine alignment every 15 frames using a coarse-to-fine Gaussian pyramid methodology (computing Scharr gradient magnitudes).

However, if abrupt camera shifts or vibrations occur, the `cc_score` plunges. The fusion loop checks:
```python
if frame_count % 15 == 0 or current_cc < 0.3:
    aligner.trigger_update(r_gray, t_gray)
```
This forces an immediate, event-driven realignment, minimizing misalignment tearing when the hardware shakes.

