## 3. Robust Video Ingestion with Exponential Backoff

RTSP network streams are prone to packet drops over wireless/IoT hardware.

**Solution:**
The [VideoStream](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260309/fire_detection/pi_fire_fusion_pipeline.py#26-72) uses the Python `collections.deque(maxlen=1)`.
- **Zero-Lag:** As opposed to stacking frames into an infinite queue which causes immense memory leaks, `maxlen=1` guarantees the thread is always capturing the most recent real-world packet. If the main loop falls behind, older frames simply drop.
- **Exponential Backoff:** If the connection terminates (`cap.read() == False`), an automatic reconnection is fired using exponentially scaling delays (`wait_time = min(60, 2 ** (self.retries + 1))`). The stale queue `self.Q.clear()` is wiped, causing the main loop to safely pause overhead logic until processing resumes.

